Objectives

After completing this lab you will be able to:

Access the Cassandra server with cqlsh, the command-line interface for using the Cassandra Query Language (CQL)
Run commands to learn more about the server and session, such as server version and host details
Determine the available keyspaces, which are objects similar to databases, on the server

Assumes you have a cassandra cluster up and running and are using the cassandra CLI

show host

This will show the details of the server you have connected to.

show version

This will show the version of the cassandra server.

describe keyspaces

This will print a list of the keyspaces present on the server.

cls

This will clear the cqlsh screen.

exit

Disconnect from cassandra server